  "name": "RPlog_Who_s_Sane_Now",
  "title": "A Crisis on the Corellia Tarmac",
  "summary": "At a Corellia spaceport, the ex-Imperial Dareus, plagued by hallucinations and intrusive thoughts since a night at the Smuggler's Dig, crosses paths with the cheerful Bith newcomer Scrat and the Jedi pilot Johanna te Danaan. When the ISB officer Korynn Fleming arrives marching a bound Sullustan prisoner, Johanna intervenes, using the Force to convince Korynn he has mistaken her identity and to free the captive. As CorSec, led by Colonel Twila Virda, swarms the restricted area, Dareus defuses the standoff at his own risk, talking down the guards and surrendering his blaster so no one is killed, while Korynn releases the Sullustan and withdraws. Afterward, Dareus follows Johanna to the abandoned old spaceport, confessing that his mind has unraveled and begging her to tell him whether someone has tampered with it. Johanna denies altering him and senses no signature of memory manipulation, suggesting instead that he is coming apart from guilt over the man he has become. Finding cold comfort in her words, Dareus resolves to stop searching for an external cause and vanishes into the shadows.",
